RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 48. Maiden Claiming Purse 14000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEULAH K vied for the lead in between competitors after the break, rated off of the pace and stalked the pace setter, launched a bid at the seven sixteenth pole ,responded willingly and drew beside the front runner at he five sixteenth pole, was immerged in a full on battle for the lead at the quarter pole, battled down the lane under heavy urging until the last sixteenth, then repelled her rival and drew away for a game win. GRACEFUL STREET showed natural early speed, raced five wide, took back and laid off the early speed and rated willingly, raced from off of the pace until the half mile pole, was given the cue and responded well, gaining ground and building momentum, circled the field through the turn in the four path, was under strong urging entering the stretch, passed the early leader after the sixteenth pole, struggled to switch leads but still finished second. SMILING ANGEL vied for the lead, took command and set the pace, was pressured by an outside foe nearing the three eighths, was challenged for the lead att the five sixteenth pole, battled past the quarter pole and into deep stretch, tired late. OUR LIL SCANDAL was off a step slow, raced four wide, improved position while racing down the back side, was in contention after the three eighths pole, edged out and was clear entering the stretch, was urged and encouraged but had no late rally. CLEARANCE SALE raced mid pack from the three path but never got involved. AFLEET CHARLENE was rank early, raced on the rail, took back and rated, tired into the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 11500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAIL SOUTHERN raced in the middle of the pack early on, advanced along the rail down the back side, stalked after the half mile pole, shifted out leaving the turn, raced in the four path was was encouraged down the lane, responded well, gained ground and built momentum, caught the leading rival after the sixteenth pole, matched strides raced eye ball to eyeball, was driven and kept on point, cleared in the last few strides to take the win. STELLAR TAP was keen and on the bit early, raced on the outside in the five path, pulled next to the leaders by the half, engaged in a three way battle near the five sixteenth pole, battled into the stretch, shook one foe at the quarter pole, repelled the other front runner nearing the sixteenth pole, was hooked by an outside rival and engaged in another battle, encouraged and urged, raced head to head, stride for stride, but just missed at the wire. CLERIC raced in the two path, between foes, held pace waw shuffled back off of the pace, launched a bid after the three eighth s pole, circled the fiield while closing ground, shifted out five wide in the upper stretch, was encouraged and closed enough to claim third. STREET ART vied for the lead, ended up stalking the pace, drew beside the leaders from in between horses near the half, stayed on and matched strides with those two foes through the turn, shook one near the quarter pole, continued to battle down the stretch then tired right before the sixteenth pole and gave way. CRAFTY HEAT vied for the led, set the pace, was joined and sett he next split with company, then tired by the quarter pole. J'S LITTLE MAN had a scrambled start, regained composure but was never involved. SOUTH AL SPARKY flashed early speed, raced between horses and faltered.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPER INTENSE showed early speed, relaxed and stalked on the outside in the five path, was allowed to moved at the half, willingly gained ground and passed rivals, was given more head through the turn, he still responded well and happily circled into the lead near the five sixteenth pole, allowed another competitor to stay beside him into the stretch,, then he drew off as he pleased. CHIEF HARLAN raced off of the pace in the two path, shifted out into the five path in the upper stretch, was under heavy encouragement and closed willingly, was no match for the winner but was definitely second best today. TRAFFIC BOSS was off a bit slow, raced four wide, was well off the pace, was in contention at the quarter pole, launched a bid and showed a tremendous turn of foot, getting up for third. DIESEL FUEL vied for the lead, set the pace, was pressured by outside foes, was challenged and tried to match strides with the eventual winner but gave way early in the stretch drive. DOCE DE LA NOCHE stalked the early pace, raced four wide, was passed by the eventual winner entering the turn, tried to match strides with that rival, dropped into the turn establishing position, but tired before the stretch. DEE'S LEGS vied for the early lead, tried to take advantage of the one post position, raced on the rail while setting the early fractions, the stopped. HE'S TROUBLE showed early speed, stalked the pace while racing three wide on the inside of another rival, this set was passed on the outside by the eventual winner, when the horse to his outside tried to g with the eventual winner entering the turn HE'S TROUBLE had to check to make room, then faded after that. SOCIAL APPEAL trailed., SOCIAL APPEAL WAS PULLED UP BEFORE THE THREE EIGHTHS POLE AND VANNED OFF.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: EL GEMAR raced off of the pace in the middle of the pack, was in the five path, launched a bid at the half mile pole, responded well to a hand ride along the back side and through the turn, was in contention in the stretch and in the four path, shifted out into the six path at the eighth pole and was given the cue, responded with a big turn of foot and closed with long fluid strides, taking the win easily in the last few jumps. PRINCE COSMO vied for the lead, pressured the inside leaders for the first set of fractions, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, matched strides and battled for the win with an inside rival, was under heavy urging into the upper stretch, cleared that rival after the eighth pole, was in command and on the lead, was caught late by a fast closing outside rival and just missed. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Alabama S. LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Stakes Purse 50000. FOR REGISTERED ALABAMA BRED THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A STAKE RACE. No nomination. No entry or start fee. $50,000 Guaranteed of which 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Weights: Three Years Old 122 lbs.; Older 124 lbs. Non winners of a race since March 24, 2023 allowed 2 lbs. Maidens are allowed 4 lbs. In the event that more than Fourteen (14) horses pass the entry box, preference will be given to the horses with the highest earnings in 20 22 - 2023. Different owners have equal draw according to earnings. The second part of same owner entries will have no consideration over a single interest. Alabama Breeders Association will present a trophy to the winning owner. Nominations Closed Monday June 12, 2023 with 12 Nominees.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FREEDOM FACTOR raced from mid pack on the rail, improved at the half on the rail, angled out at the quarter pole, closed down the stretch, collared the early leaders at the eighth pole, held on for the win. OPTIMUS KAT vied for the lead from in between horses, rated just off of the pace, settled even further back through the turn, launched a bid at the quarter pole, responded well and closed well under strong encouragement, split horses in the last sixteenth of a mile, and was up for second with an impressive drive. I'M D'CAT settled off of the pace in hands in the three path, advanced at the half mile pole, was cued and responded well at the quarter pole, closed ground and improved position with every stride, struggled to switch leads by still ran a game third. AZTAR vied for the the lead from the three path, set the pace in a set of three, improved position from in between horses through the turn, battled for the lead down the stretch, faltered after the sixteenth pole. AFTER AZTAR CROSSED THE FINISH LINE HE WAS PULLED UP AND VANNED OFF. RUN ROCKET trailed early, mild improvement. HOSTILE AFLEET flashed early speed then faltered. FETCHS BRAHM made no impact.
